images.title: Full moon in December
images.caption: Full moon
images.desc: Each month of the year has at least one full moon, and the occasion of that full moon often has nicknames related to the season. In the Northern Hemisphere, December is usually considered the start of winter, so December's first full moon gets the chilly nickname 'cold moon.' It's sometimes called the 'long night moon,' since the winter solstice is just around the corner.
